title.narrative: IN Maharashtra Water Sector Improvement Project

description.narrative: The project development objectives are: (i) to strengthen the state's capacity for multi-sectoral planning, development and sustainable management of the water resources; and (ii) to improve irrigation service delivery and productivity of irrigated agriculture.

condition.narrative: For purposes of Part B of the project, Maharashtra shall ensure that dam safety works shall be carried out only after theclearanceof these works by dam safety panels.
In cases of voluntary acquisition of land, Maharashtra shall ensure that such land is provided in accordance with a MOU agreedwiththe Bank, the WUA, a representative of Maharashtra and land owner.
Maharashtra shall carry out Part B of the project in accordance with the Social and Environmental Management Framework in a mannersatisfactory to the Bank.
Maharashtra shall ensure that rehabilitation & modernization work of canal systems in all the minor schemes & at minor andtertiarylevel in medium and major schemes will be carried out thru CMC
Maharashtra shall implement bulk supply and volumetric charging of irrigation water to Water Users Associations in accordance withtheir entitlement in six selected pilot schemes
Maharashtra shall in accordance with the provisions of the MWRRA Act 2005, establish Maharashtra Water Resources RegulatoryAuthority by Dec 31, 2005 and make it operational.
Maharashtra shall make adequate budgetary allocation on a yearly basis for each Fiscal Year to meet the operation and maintenancecosts of irrigation schemes under the Project
Maharashtra shall make fully operational, the Project Preparation and Management Unit (PPMU) and thereafter maintain the PPMUwithin the WRD with multidisciplinary staff in adequate number
Maharashtra shall prepare a project evaluation report with TORs satisfactory to the Bank, to integrate M&E activities formonitoring project performance.
Maharashtra shall prepare an evaluation report with TORs satisfactory to the Bank, with recommended measures for efficient projectperformance and achievement of PDOs.
Maharashtra shall rationalize water charges including irrigation charges to meet in each year the full operation and maintenancecosts of irrigation schemes
Maharashtra shall reorganize the Maharashtra Krishna Valley Dev. Corp. into a river basin agency to be known as MaharashtraKrishnaValley Water Resources Corp. in accordance with MWRRA Act 2005.
Maharashtra through its WR Dept and in respect of irrigation schemes under the Project, shall support, foster and oversee theformation of DLA, CLA and PLAs in all other schemes
Maharashtra through its WR Dept and in respect of the irrigation schemes under the Project, shall support, foster and oversee theformation of Water Users Assocatiions at all minor levels
Restructure the water resources department in accordance with the objectives set out in Maharashtra State Water Policy

title.narrative: Improved water use efficiency at the scheme levels.

baseline.value: 78.5 hectares per Mm3 of water at scheme level

comment.narrative: Figure revised based on data analysis and field verifications

target.value: 102 hectares per Mm3 of water at scheme level (30% increase)

comment.narrative: The achievement is more than the target.
This is the gross area irrigated.

title.narrative: Improved collection efficiency of irrigation water charges

actual.value: a) 37.86% at state levelb) 58.52% under the project

comment.narrative: These are provisional figures as data for all the schemes are under collection.

title.narrative: About 1707 number of Water User Organisations (WUOs) established in targeted 236 irrigation schemes

target.value: All the 1674 WUOs established in the targeted 235 irrigation schemes

actual.value: Second term elections of the WUOs are under way and are scheduled to be completed by February 28, 2014.

title.narrative: Six of pilot schemes with volumetric charging and bulk supply of water as per entitlement in the Krishna Basin.

target.value: volumetric charging and bulk supply started in six pilot schemes.

actual.value: All the pilots completed and volumetric supply started

title.narrative: Operationalization of Maharashtra Water Resources Regulatory Authority (MWRRA) - adequate staffing and budget allocation

target.value: All the units of MWRRA established; at least 90% designated staff are in place; and annual budget allocated.

actual.value: MWRRA already established and operational with 66% staffing and budget allocations.

title.narrative: Restructuring of Maharashtra Krishna Valley Development Authority (MKVDC) into "Maharashtra Krishna Valley Water Resources Corporation (MKVWRC)"

target.value: Restructuring likely to be completed by March 28, 2014

comment.narrative: With only 5 months of the project period left, there is no possibility of any progress on this.
